# ACL CISCO / PACKET TRACER

## Configuration interface routeur

```bash
enable
configure terminal

interface gigabitEthernet 0/0
ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
no shutdown

end
copy running-config startup-config
```

---

# VÉRIFICATION

```bash
show ip interface brief
show running-config
show access-lists
```

---

# ACL STANDARD

## Autoriser uniquement 192.168.1.10

```bash
access-list 1 permit 192.168.1.10
access-list 1 deny any
```

Application :

```bash
interface gigabitEthernet 0/0
ip access-group 1 in
```

---

# ACL ÉTENDUE

## Autoriser HTTP et HTTPS

```bash
access-list 100 permit tcp any host 192.168.1.10 eq 80
access-list 100 permit tcp any host 192.168.1.10 eq 443
```

## Bloquer SSH

```bash
access-list 100 deny tcp any host 192.168.1.10 eq 22
```

## Bloquer tout le reste

```bash
access-list 100 deny ip any any
```

Application :

```bash
interface gigabitEthernet 0/0
ip access-group 100 in
```

---

# ACL ICMP (PING)

## Bloquer le ping

```bash
access-list 100 deny icmp any any
```

## Autoriser le ping

```bash
access-list 100 permit icmp any any
```

---

# SUPPRIMER UNE ACL

## Supprimer une ACL complète

```bash
no access-list 100
```

## Retirer une ACL d'une interface

```bash
interface gigabitEthernet 0/0
no ip access-group 100 in
```

